Program: Omnibus
Title: 33 Days
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376kp5
Last Broadcast Date: 28 September 1993
Albino Luciani, the new Pope lasted only 33 days before he died in reportedly mysterious circumstances. The programme looks at the unexpectedness of his election, how little was know about him and the rumours that circulated after his death.